  "text": "The glucose uptake rate was measured using the glucose assay kit (glucose oxidase method) according to the published procedure with some modification [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the insulin-resistant HepG2 cells were cultured in serum-free, high-glucose DMEM with or without BDDE at the specified concentrations or metformin (10 μM) for 24 h. After 24 h, the glucose concentration in the culture medium was measured using the glucose assay kit. The glucose uptake rate was calculated by subtracting the glucose concentration at the end of the culture period from the glucose concentration of the high-glucose DMEM. MTT assay was performed to adjust the errors generated from cell number difference.",
